Site was dropped in the spring of 2020 because of repeated reports (in 2018 and 2019) of staff encountering creepy men at or near the area staff parked. In 2019 staff encountered a man who was living out of his van at the site. In 2018, staff encountered a bow hunter who tried to convince them to get to the site via an alternative path. Given how remote the site is, Kate M decided to drop the site rather than have staff be nervous/apprehensive about sampling the site. Notes about site location: Keep left for 0.7 miles after passing second gate (near power plant) on Rattlesnake Rd. . Take the first road on the right, overgrown logging road, drive to the very end (0.2 mi) and park. Find the remains of an old road to the West (now very overgrown) and follow the game trail until the road bends right, turn left (on game trail) for ~500 ft and head downhill to the stream. There is a very large, tall cedar snag near the sample site. This is a 10-20 minute walk and should be flagged with pink flagging.
